turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You're the only one I know who loves his parents.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I know it went out of style didn't it?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: It's okay.  It's a good thing.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You know it's lovely here.  The air is sweet.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You're not sorry you came.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Not sorry, no but I'm not staying.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Why?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: In the first place, your mother as much as told me to go.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Well.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You saw that and you- you've been kind of-

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: What?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Well kind of embarrassed ever since I got here.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: The trouble is I planned on sneaking up on you over a period of a week or so but they take it for granted that we're all set.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I knew they would, your mother anyway.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: How did you know?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: From her point of view why else would I come?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Wouldn't you want to?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I guess you know this is why I asked you to come.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I guess this is why I came.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Ann, I love you.  I love you a great deal.  I love you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I have no imagination that's all I know to tell you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I'm embarrassing you.  I didn't want to tell it to you here.  I

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: wanted some place we'd never been, a place where we'd be brand new to each other.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You think this is wrong, this chair, this yard.  I want you to be ready for me.  I don't want to win you away from anything.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Chris, I've been ready a long, long time.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: And he's gone forever.  You're sure?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I almost got married two years ago.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Why didn't you?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You started to write me.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You felt something that far back?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Every day since.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Ann, why didn't you let me know?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I was waiting for you, Chris.  Till then you never wrote and then when you did what did you say.  I mean you sure can be ambiguous you know.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Give me a kiss, Ann.  Give me a-God I kissed you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I kissed Annie.  How long, how long I've been waiting to kiss you.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: I'll never forgive you.  Why did you wait all these years?  All I've done is sit and wonder if I was crazy for thinking of you.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Annie, we're going to live now.  I'm going to make you so happy.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Not like that you're not.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I kissed you.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Like Larry's brother.  Do it like you, Chris.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: What is it Chris?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Let's drive some place.  I want to be alone with you.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: No.  What is it Chris, your mother?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: No, nothing like that.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Well then what's wrong?  Even in your letters there was something ashamed.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Yes.  I suppose I have been but it's going from me.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You've got to tell me.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I don't know where to start.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: It wouldn't work this way.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: There's so many things mixed up.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: You remember overseas I was in command of a company?

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Yeah, sure.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Well I lost them.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: How many?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Just about all.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Oh, gees.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: It takes a lot of time to toss that off because they weren't just men.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: For instance, one time it had been raining several days and this kid came to me and gave me his last pair of dry socks.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I put them in my pocket. that's only a little thing but these are the kind of guys I had.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: They didn't die.  They killed themselves for each other.  I mean that exactly.  A little more selfish and they'd have been here today.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: And I got this idea watching them go down.  Everything was being destroyed see, but it seemed to me that there was one new thing that was made

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: a sort of responsibility man for man.  You understand me?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: And then I came home and it was amazing.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: There was no meaning in it here.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: The whole thing to them was sort of a bus accident. Then I went to work with father and that whole rat race again.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I felt, what you said, ashamed somehow

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: because nobody was changed at all.  It seemed to make suckers out of a lot of guys.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I felt wrong to be alive, to open the new bank book, to drive the new car, to see the new refrigerator.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I mean you can take those things out of war but

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: when you drive the new car, you have to know that it came out of the love a man can have for a man.  You've got to be a little better because of that.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Otherwise what you have is really just loot and there's blood on it.  I didn't want to take any of it.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I guess that included you.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: And do you still feel that way?

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: I want you now, Annie.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: Because you mustn't feel that way anymore because you have a right to whatever you have, Chris, do you understand, everything

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: that includes me.  And your money there's nothing wrong in your money.  Your father put hundreds of planes in the air.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: You should be proud.  A man should be paid for that.

turns.speaker: M
turns.content: Annie, Annie I'm going to make a fortune for you.

turns.speaker: F
turns.content: What'll I do with a fortune?
